{
  "article_id": "TheSacredHeartReview1898",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "Under the title of \"Our Seaboard Islands on the Pacific,\" "
      },
      {
        "text": "Mr. John E. Bennett",
        "entity_key": "jbe",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " contributes to "
      },
      {
        "text": "this same magazine",
        "entity_key": "sacheartrev",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " a very interesting and instructive paper dealing with "
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands that lie off the Californian coast",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and which are known as "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Farallones",
        "entity_key": "i_far",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "Of one of these islands, ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", he tells us that long before their discovery by ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Cabrillo",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "jca",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in 1542, ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "this particular island",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " was overrun by the ",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Innuit Indians",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "rfurcompany",
          "natam_inuit"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who came down from the North, killed all the men, and carried off all things that they thought of any value, leaving only the women and children behind them.",
        "tropes": [
          11
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The original inhabitants",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " of ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "these islands",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " are described by ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Cabrillo",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "jca",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " as ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a mild, but vigorous race",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": " The woman and children left on "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " maintained themselves after the Innuit invasion, and "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " again became peopled. In 1835 some "
      },
      {
        "text": "Franciscan missionaries",
        "entity_keys": [
          "misfats",
          "ndur",
          "aji"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " came to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " from "
      },
      {
        "text": "California",
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " and persuaded "
      },
      {
        "text": "the islanders",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " to remove to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mainland",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " and reside at "
      },
      {
        "text": "the missions",
        "entity_key": "mi_mainlandmissions",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". When "
      },
      {
        "text": "the boats",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " had left "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "one woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " discovered that "
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " had been overlooked and left behind. "
      },
      {
        "text": "She jumped from ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the boat",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " and swam back to ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", where she and ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were then the only inhbaitants.",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The child",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " died soon afterwards, but "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mother",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " lived to an advanced age, and near the end of her days she was brought to the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara mission",
        "entity_key": "mi_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", at which her death took place."
      }
    ]
  ]
}